<subSubSection id="6DC56513FFECFFE0E292A0D1CA0A70A3" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="25603698FFECFFE0E292A0D1CDBE76BB" blockId="2.[151,1437,695,1226]" box="[151,1022,695,722]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E292A0D1CF7276BB" bold="true" box="[151,306,695,721]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">
<typeStatus id="FA64883AFFECFFE0E292A0D1CE9276BB" box="[151,210,695,721]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E33CA0D1CCA976B8" authority="Carpenter, 1935" authorityName="Carpenter" authorityYear="1935" box="[313,745,695,722]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creedei">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E33CA0D1CC6B76BB" box="[313,555,695,721]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Palaeochrysa creedei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFECFFE0E036A0D1CCA976B8" author="Carpenter, F. M." box="[563,745,695,722]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="259 - 271" refId="ref22778" refString="Carpenter, F. M. (1935) Tertiary insects of the family Chrysopidae. Journal of Paleontology, 9, 259 - 271." type="journal article" year="1935">Carpenter, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25603698FFECFFE0E2C2A0BDCD40707F" blockId="2.[151,1437,695,1226]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E2C2A0BDCFF9769F" bold="true" box="[199,441,731,757]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Emended diagnosis.</emphasis>
May be distinguished from other genera of 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E1C3A0BDCA37769F" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1910" box="[966,1143,731,757]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Nothochrysinae">Nothochrysinae</taxonomicName>
by a combination of the following. Forewing: (1) M forked far distad origin of RP [other genera: proximad to slightly distad]; (2) one crossvein between RA, RP proximad 1r-m present [other genera: absent]; (3) 
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E606A142CA5F7757" box="[1027,1055,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">im</emphasis>
relatively narrow, elongate [
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E761A142CFF7770B" authority="Schluter, 1982" authorityName="Schluter" authorityYear="1982" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Cimbrochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E761A142CF48770B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Cimbrochrysa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFECFFE0E315A121CFF7770B" author="Schluter, T." box="[272,439,839,865]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="257 - 264" refId="ref25389" refString="Schluter, T. (1982) Cimbrochrysa moleriensis n. g. n. sp. und Hypochrysa hercyniensis n. sp., zwei fossile Chrysopidae-Arten (Insecta: Planipennia) aus dem europaischen Tertiar. Neues Jahrbuch fur Geologie und Palaontologie, Monatshefte, 5, 257 - 264. https: // doi. org / 10.1127 / njgpm / 1982 / 1982 / 257" type="journal article" year="1982">Schlüter, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E3C6A121CD46770B" authority="Wilmann, 1993" authorityName="Wilmann" authorityYear="1993" box="[451,774,839,865]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Danochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E3C6A121CC0C770B" box="[451,588,839,865]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Danochrysa</emphasis>
Wilmann, 1993
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E114A121CA0D770B" authority="Makarkin, 2014" authorityName="Makarkin" authorityYear="2014" box="[785,1101,839,865]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Asiachrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E114A121CDCD770B" box="[785,909,839,865]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Asiachrysa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFECFFE0E193A121CA0D770B" author="Makarkin V. N." box="[918,1101,839,865]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref24254" refString="Makarkin V. N. (2014) A new fossil green lacewing (Neuroptera: Chrysopidae) from the Eocene Tadushi Formation, eastern Sikhote-Alin. Far Eastern Entomologist, 272, 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="2014">Makarkin, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E65FA121CF3377EF" authority="Makarkin &amp; Archibald, 2013" authorityName="Makarkin &amp; Archibald" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Okanaganochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E65FA121CB67770B" box="[1114,1319,839,865]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Okanaganochrysa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFECFFE0E72AA121CF3377EF" author="Makarkin, V. N. &amp; Archibald, S. B." pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="123 - 146" refId="ref24341" refString="Makarkin, V. N. &amp; Archibald, S. B. (2013) A diverse new assemblage of green lacewings (Insecta: Neuroptera: Chrysopidae) from the Early Eocene Okanagan Highlands, western North America. Journal of Paleontology, 87, 123 - 146. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 12 - 052 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2013">Makarkin &amp; Archibald, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E387A10DCC4C77EF" authorityName="Adams &amp; Penny" authorityYear="1992" box="[386,524,875,901]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Leptochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E387A10DCC4C77EF" box="[386,524,875,901]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Leptochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: broadly pentagonal; 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E108A10DCDD477EF" authorityName="Hagen" authorityYear="1966" box="[781,916,875,901]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Hypochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E108A10DCDD477EF" box="[781,916,875,901]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Hypochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E1A3A10DCA0B77EF" authorityName="Adams &amp; Penny" authorityYear="1992" box="[934,1099,875,901]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Asthenochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E1A3A10DCA0B77EF" box="[934,1099,875,901]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Asthenochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: broadly triangular]; (4) two gradate series in radial space [
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E3F0A1E9CC8277C3" authorityName="Makarkin &amp; Archibald" authorityYear="2013" box="[501,706,911,937]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Okanaganochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E3F0A1E9CC8277C3" box="[501,706,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Okanaganochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E0D6A1E9CD2277C3" authorityName="Kimmins" authorityYear="1952" box="[723,866,911,937]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Triplochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E0D6A1E9CD2277C3" box="[723,866,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Triplochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: three; 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E1B8A1E9CA1277C3" authorityName="Esben-Petersen" authorityYear="1917" box="[957,1106,911,937]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Dictyochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E1B8A1E9CA1277C3" box="[957,1106,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Dictyochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E667A1E9CF1077A7" authority="Makarkin &amp; Archibald, 2013" authorityName="Makarkin &amp; Archibald" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Adamsochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E667A1E9CB4777C3" box="[1122,1287,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Adamsochrysa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFECFFE0E715A1E9CF1077A7" author="Makarkin, V. N. &amp; Archibald, S. B." pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="123 - 146" refId="ref24341" refString="Makarkin, V. N. &amp; Archibald, S. B. (2013) A diverse new assemblage of green lacewings (Insecta: Neuroptera: Chrysopidae) from the Early Eocene Okanagan Highlands, western North America. Journal of Paleontology, 87, 123 - 146. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 12 - 052 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2013">Makarkin &amp; Archibald, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: four or more]. Hind wing: (5) MA not fused with RP (connecting by crossvein 1r-m) [other genera: fused (except 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E337A1B1CFFC779B" authorityName="Adams &amp; Penny" authorityYear="1992" box="[306,444,983,1009]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Leptochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E337A1B1CFFC779B" box="[306,444,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Leptochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E3CCA1B1CD7B779B" authority="Wilmann, 1993" authorityName="Wilmann" authorityYear="1993" box="[457,827,982,1009]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Stephenbrooksia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E3CCA1B1CCC3779B" box="[457,643,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Stephenbrooksia</emphasis>
Wilmann, 1993
</taxonomicName>
)]; (6) MP not fused with CuA (connecting by crossvein 2m-cu) [probably all other genera: fused or contacting]
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25603698FFECFFE0E2C2A679CB1470CF" blockId="2.[151,1437,695,1226]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E2C2A679CFD47053" bold="true" box="[199,404,1055,1081]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Species included.</emphasis>
Six species: 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFECFFE0E02DA679CAD07053" authority="Makarkin &amp; Archibald, 2013" authorityName="Makarkin &amp; Archibald" authorityYear="2013" box="[552,1168,1055,1081]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Archaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="profracta">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFECFFE0E02DA679CD027053" box="[552,834,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Archaeochrysa profracta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFECFFE0E14CA679CAD07053" author="Makarkin, V. N. &amp; Archibald, S. B." box="[841,1168,1055,1081]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="123 - 146" refId="ref24341" refString="Makarkin, V. N. &amp; Archibald, S. B. (2013) A diverse new assemblage of green lacewings (Insecta: Neuroptera: Chrysopidae) from the Early Eocene Okanagan Highlands, western North America. Journal of Paleontology, 87, 123 - 146. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 12 - 052 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2013">Makarkin &amp; Archibald, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
